@Node "_BackGroundIO"
_BackGroundIO-Route I/O to the console window

Synopsis

   long _BackGroundIO;

Description

   _BackGroundIO is used by cback.o to indicate whether output will be
   sent to the console window by your background process.  The default is
   0, indicating that I/O will not be sent to the console window.

   This variable is of interest only for background processes.  If you do
   not link with cback.o, this variable is ignored.

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

