@Node "__ctype"
__ctype-Character class table

Synopsis

   #include <ctype.h>

Description

   The external character array __ctype is a table indicating the
   attributes of all ASCII characters.   It is 257 bytes long; one byte
   per ASCII character.  The individual bits within the byte are set to
   indicate attributes as described below.

        Bit     Value   Meaning
        ---     -----   -------
        _U      0x01    Upper-case alphabetic character (A-Z)
        _L      0x02    Lower-case alphabetic character (a-z)
        _N      0x04    Decimal digit (0-9)
        _S      0x08    White space
        _P      0x10    Punctuation character
        _C      0x20    Control character
        _B      0x40    Blank
        _X      0x80    Hexadecimal digit (0-9, A-F, a-f)

   All indexes are offset by one so that the table also handles the
   end-of-file character (-1).  You must index the table by the character
   plus one.  Normally, you will not need to access the array directly,
   but will instead use the is...() character test macros (@{" isupper() " Link "isupper()"},
   @{" isascii() " Link "isascii()"}, and others) to access it for you.

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

   @{" isalnum() " Link "isalnum()"} , @{" isalpha() " Link "isalpha()"} , @{" isascii() " Link "isascii()"} , @{" iscntrl() " Link "iscntrl()"} ,
   @{" iscsym() " Link "iscsym()"} , @{" iscsymf() " Link "iscsymf()"} , @{" isdigit() " Link "isdigit()"} , @{" isgraph() " Link "isgraph()"} ,
   @{" islower() " Link "islower()"} , @{" isprint() " Link "isprint()"} , @{" ispunct() " Link "ispunct()"} , @{" isspace() " Link "isspace()"} ,
   @{" isupper() " Link "isupper()"} , @{" isxdigit() " Link "isxdigit()"}
@EndNode

