findpath()-Locate file in the current path

Synopsis

   #include <dos.h>

   lock = findpath(filename);

   BPTR lock;
   const char *filename;

Portability

   AmigaDOS

Returns

   If findpath() finds the file, it returns a lock on that directory even
   if it is the current directory.  The lock must be unlocked with the
   AmigaDOS @{" UnLock() " Link "dos/UnLock()"} function.  If findpath() cannot find the file, it
   returns a -1.  NULL is not used because it is a valid lock.

