@Node "__fmode"
__fmode-Default level 2 I/O mode

Synopsis

   extern int __fmode;

Description

   This external integer is used by the @{" fopen() " Link "fopen()"} function to determine
   the translation mode to use when the programmer does not specify a mode
   in the @{" fopen() " Link "fopen()"} call.  For AmigaDOS, it is set to 0x8000, which
   specifies untranslated mode.

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

   @{" fopen() " Link "fopen()"}
@EndNode

