@Node "_FPERR"
_FPERR-Floating Point Error Code

Synopsis

   extern int _FPERR;

Description

   This location contains a non-zero value after any low-level floating
   point operation encounters an error.  Low-level operations include
   addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, comparison, and
   conversion from one number representation to another (for example,
   float to double).

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

   @{" _CXFERR() " Link "_CXFERR()"}
@EndNode

