@Node "getasn()"
getasn()-Get assigned device

Synopsis

   #include <dos.h>

   dlist = getasn(name);

   struct DeviceList *dlist; /* pointer to device list entry */
                             /* for assignment               */
   const char *name;         /* assigned name                */

Portability

   AmigaDOS

Returns

   NULL is returned if name cannot be located in the device list.  NULL is
   defined in stddef.h.  If the name is found, a pointer to the name's
   device node is returned.  Some pointers in the device node are BCPL
   pointers, and strings are BCPL strings.  See dos/dosextens.h for more
   information.

