@Node "_MNEED"
_MNEED-minimum Dynamic Memory Needed

Synopsis

   extern long _MNEED;  /* to reference default value */
   long _MNEED = n;     /* to set initial value */

Description

   _MNEED indicates the minimum number of bytes that must be provided as
   the heap space for use by the various memory allocators.  This space,
   whose size is rounded up to be an even multiple of @{" _MSTEP " Link "_MSTEP"}, is the
   initial block of memory in the local memory pool.

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

    @{" calloc() " Link "calloc()"} , @{" malloc() " Link "malloc()"} , @{" _MSTEP " Link "_MSTEP"}
@EndNode

