@Node "__nufbs"
__nufbs-Count of level 1 file handle slots

Synopsis

   #include <ios1.h>
   extern int __nufbs;

Description

   The external integer __nufbs indicates how many level 1 file handle
   slots are available in the __ufbs array.  By default, this number is
   40, although you can declare a larger __ufbs structure and __nufbs
   count in your program.  Setting __nufbs does not affect the number of
   file handles because storage must be allocated.

   In versions 5.10 and earlier, this data name was called _nufbs.

Portability

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

See Also

