@Node "__sigfunc()"
__sigfunc()-signal() function table

Synopsis

   #include <signal.h>

   extern void (*__sigfunc[NSIG])(int);

Description

   __sigfunc is the array of all signal handles.  When the @{" raise() " Link "raise()"}
   function is called, it looks in the table to see what is installed at
   the corresponding slot in the __sigfunc array.  Each entry is either a
   pointer to the function to be called when the event occurs or one of
   two special values:

        SIG_IGN         Ignore the condition.
        SIG_DFL         Take the default action.

   You should not set elements of this array directly.  Use the @{" signal() " Link "signal()"}
   function instead.

Portability

   @{" UNIX " Link "Glossary - UNIX"}

See Also

   @{" raise() " Link "raise()"} , @{" signal() " Link "signal()"}
@EndNode

@Node "signal()"
signal()-Establish event traps

Synopsis

   #include <signal.h>

   oldfun = signal(sig,newfun);

   void (*oldfun)(int);  /* old trap function */
   int sig;              /* signal() number */
   void (*newfun)(int);  /* new trap function */

Portability

   @{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"}

Returns

   If the trap can be established, the signal() function returns a pointer
   to the previous handler function.  Otherwise, it returns SIG_ERR and
   places error information in @{" errno " Link "errno"}.
@EndNode

