@Node "_STRICT_ANSI"
_STRICT_ANSI-Define to disable non-@{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"} features

Synopsis

   #define _STRICT_ANSI

Portibility

   @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"}

Description

   To be completely @{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"}-compliant, an implementation must not define any
   non-@{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"} symbols in an @{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"} header file unless the symbols begin with
   an underscore followed by a capital letter, or an underscore followed
   by another underscore.

   Defining this symbol will prevent the definition of any symbols from
   the @{" SAS/C " Link "Glossary - SASC"} Development system headers which do not comply with the @{" ANSI " Link "Glossary - ANSI"}
   standard.
@EndNode

