   extern char *_TZ;

Description

   This variable is the default time zone that is used if there is no
   environment variable TZ set on the Amiga.  If you set it, you must make
   sure that the memory for it is not freed until you reset it.  If _TZ is
   not set to any value, CST6 is used instead.

